                             \/ K - K E Y L O G \/

K by itself closes the current log file, subject to confirmation.

"K -" displays what the current log file is.

"K {filename}" closes the current log file (if any) and starts logging to {file}

Logging is always to the end of a file.

Logging behaviour is affected bu modes 8, 9 & 0: see "H FM".
